	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			This spell is GREAT in conjunction with your HP-to-MANA conversion spells (allure, call of bones, deadman walking, etc). ALSO... it will continue to give you HPs AFTER the critter is dead.... thus making it easy to keep your ALLURE-type spells going well past the death of the critter.<BR>
<BR>
Giant Killing Tactic (at 35th or so, with VoS, VampCurse, BoilBlood, Root, Call of Bones, and SOW/JBoots)- Hit (hill/sand)Giant with VoS... Run until giant is out of range... stop and keep pressing &quot;root&quot; hotkey until spell casts (giant in range again)... if resisted, run again, but if rooted, Boil, Call of Bones, VoS again (should be 40seconds to this point), then VampCurse. Keep repeating the run / root / VoS with VampCurse thrown in when needed. Keep Call of Bones on until after fight, unless you can't get VampCurse to cast (shouldn't be a problem). Watch your HPs!<BR>
<BR>
After the initial round, always make VampCurse your priority IF IT HAS WORN OFF. Obviously, if your VampCurse icon is still displayed, don't re-cast it.<BR>
<BR>
Ive been solo-ing giants from 35 to 40 so far, and the ONLY time i was killed is when a second giant joined in the chase and i didn't notice it. I rooted one, thought OK... lets start DOT'ing, then WHAM! Number two stunned me and spun me and i just couldn't get away... oh well. <BR>
<BR>
I'll make HUNDREDS of platinum per hour, unless there's a big group of non-necros in oasis taking my cash cows away from me (hehe). No-one can believe i solo'ed them under 40, but its true!<BR>
<BR>
The biggest pain is a Druid who thinks he's doing you a favor by ensnaring the giant... While its nice to think that a slow giant is a good giant, what happens is that, as soon as you get &quot;out of range&quot;, the giant turns on the druid.... the druid thinks &quot;dang! gotta get out of here&quot;, and makes a cheetah-speed run for it. Off goes your giant after Mr. Druid, and you're left wondering where your prey is. Eh, time to zone, come back, and resume your hunt.<BR>
<BR>
Also, a little &quot;trick&quot; of mine is this- GIANTs LOSE SPEED RUNNING DOWNHILL! Yes, its TRUE! If you need to get away, don't head across the flats of Oasis, run up and down the dunes. Sure, you may take a few HPs in falling damage, but the giant will be slowed to a fraction of its normal speed. WHY? I couldn't say. All i know is that its true. God (Innoruuk?) Bless the Dunes!<BR>
<BR>
OK. that's enough from me. Happy Hunting!
			</font>
	
		</td>
	</tr>
	
